node.text:
In this episode, @rvca_womens and @rvcasurf advocate Sage Erickson talks about what it was like growing up in the California country and being uprooted at a young age. She also shares her experience entering the surf world later than most, rising to become a U.S. Open of Surfing champion as well as what it’s like working with brands that value strength over beauty and individuality over conformity. Watch as this California Girl takes us on a locals tour of her Central Coast hometown and gives us an inside look into her grounded and grateful life, in the latest installment of RVCA Q&A. #balanceofopposites

Video | @blainesuque
Cover Image | @williekessel

node.text: Ive felt ive had some of my best surfing happen this year.. just waiting for that one moment to click to round out the 2021 season with a bang  @wsl - thanks to @buellsurf for the BEST wetsuits snd keeping me warm! 🤙🏼to @miniblanchard for the video at home! Still at it even if its not pumping 🌊 @buell_akow @buellsurfshop

Quick dive into a few moments in the gym recently- making things light hearted is key for me because its the atmosphere i best thrive in, unless its some phyco high pressure situation, thats my other fav : @kylebakerfitness - @coconutcomradery squad goals! 💪🏼

node.text: Happy birthday diggy @lucyskupien 💜 love you so much today and every day. Id choose you a 1000 x over as one of my forevers. You teach me tons, you push me and my brain, you are fiery, fiesty and a ball of great energy! You work your ass off, hustle and freakin make shit happen. Its inspiring, especially when alls i want to do is take a nap! Here’s to sharing some joy from the last 2 days of celebrating you and your beautiful heart. Many more to come! Gods so for youuuuu and your drive to see im just here to walk it out with you!
